Why does this need sh?  It is only making one call, isn't it?
Please add a script for these if we need to do multiple steps.
No.  Don't store state in random /tmp files.
No need for sh.  Optionally add a script.
What are the conditions where this isn't done from the device tree?  Please leave some comments at a minimum.  It isn't obvious to me why we have to re-bind this device.
We have added it in the DTS, but the CPLD enables the mux when powered on to avoid access when the retimer boots up. Therefore, we need to rebind it.
We need some comments as to what this is doing and why.

GPIOZ6 is a hardware strap pin; when set high, it enables GPIO passthrough for the GPIOP group (power button in and reset in). Minerva uses the same SCM board as GTT, which is designed for debug presence pin, so its default value is pulled high.
How does the title get messed up again?
Sorry! I change it by web, not modify it in my local. Fixed it. Thanks.
